<title>≠kagara and !haunu</title>
<summary><i>≠kágára and !haunu, who fought each other with lightning. By /han≠kass’o (L VIII.-30 8637-8648). </i>≠kagara (a bird who was formerly a man) goes to !haunu (who is a rain&apos;s person) to take back his younger sister (!haunu&apos;s wife) and return her to her parents. There follows a fight (with lightning and thunder) and blood issuing from the nostrils of !haunu. </summary><comments>1) p.8636v: |han≠kass&apos;o heard this story from his maternal grandmother (≠kammi) and his mother (|xabbi-an) after his grandmother&apos;s death; the <i>≠kagara</i> bird; accounting for !haunu&apos;s name: he is a rain-sorcerer; &apos;rain (he) was&apos;, 2) p.8637v: names and descriptions of plants and lizards, 3) pp.8641v &amp; 8643v: fighting, 4) p.8642v: see <i>≠kagara&apos;s fight with !haunu in the east</i>, 5) p.8644v: see <i>Lightning which is black, it is that which kills us</i>, 6) This story is found in Book VIII-30</comments><date>24 July 1879 (started)</date><storypages>8637-8648</storypages><category>The Rain and Rain&apos;s water</category><category>History (Early Race)</category><author>|han≠kass'o (Klein Jantje) (VIII)</author><keyword><kw>rain</kw><subkw>≠kagara and !haunu</subkw></keyword>
